       <h1 class="home-featured-header">
        Featured
       </h1>
      </div>
      <article class="group home-featured-item" id="post-18259">
       <figure class="home-featured-thumbnail">
        <a href="http://complit.berkeley.edu/featured/summer-featured-course/" rel="bookmark" title="Permalink to Summer 2019 Featured Course – “Boroughs and Barrios” with Karina Palau">
         <img alt="" class="attachment-smportrait size-smportrait wp-post-image" height="200" sizes="(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px" src="http://complit.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Karina_Palau-150x200.jpg" srcset="http://complit.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Karina_Palau-150x200.jpg 150w, http://complit.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Karina_Palau-113x150.jpg 113w, http://complit.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Karina_Palau-100x133.jpg 100w, http://complit.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Karina_Palau.jpg 200w" width="150">
         </img>
        </a>
       </figure>
       <header class="home-featured-item-header">
        <h1 class="home-featured-item-title">
         <a href="http://complit.berkeley.edu/featured/summer-featured-course/" rel="bookmark" title="Permalink to Summer 2019 Featured Course – “Boroughs and Barrios” with Karina Palau">
          Summer 2019 Featured Course – “Boroughs and Barrios” with Karina Palau
         </a>
        </h1>
       </header>
       <!-- .entry-header -->
       <p>
        Karina Palau is offering her online course W60AC again this summer, “Boroughs and Barrios:  Moving In &amp; Through New York City and Los Angeles”, which will be session C (June 24-August 16th).   This will meet the American Cultures requirement, and since it is online, it can be taken anywhere in the world!  Below is the course description, while
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1w2tKDDqHV8">
         here is an introductory video
        </a>
        .  Additionally, Karina has received the “Excellence in Advising Award” for faculty for 2018-19, congratulations Karina!
       </p>
       <p>
        The Statue of Liberty with welcome torch always raised. The Hollywood sign against golden California hills. Subways and freeways running like arteries above and below ground, offering to transport us around and across the city. Many iconic images of New York City and Los Angeles construct U.S. urban centers as a space of endless movement and possibility.
        <a class="more-link" href="http://complit.berkeley.edu/featured/summer-featured-course/#more-18259">
         » Read on »
        </a>
       </p>
      </article>
      <article class="group home-featured-item" id="post-17931">
       <figure class="home-featured-thumbnail">
        <a href="http://complit.berkeley.edu/featured/featured-alumna-yvonne-lin/" rel="bookmark" title="Permalink to Alumna Spotlight:  Yvonne Lin">
         <img alt="" class="attachment-smportrait size-smportrait wp-post-image" height="198" sizes="(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px" src="http://complit.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/yvonne.lin_-150x198.jpg" srcset="http://complit.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/yvonne.lin_-150x198.jpg 150w, http://complit.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/yvonne.lin_-114x150.jpg 114w, http://complit.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/yvonne.lin_-228x300.jpg 228w, http://complit.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/yvonne.lin_-768x1012.jpg 768w, http://complit.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/yvonne.lin_-777x1024.jpg 777w, http://complit.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/yvonne.lin_-100x132.jpg 100w" width="150">
         </img>
        </a>
       </figure>
       <header class="home-featured-item-header">
        <h1 class="home-featured-item-title">
         <a href="http://complit.berkeley.edu/featured/featured-alumna-yvonne-lin/" rel="bookmark" title="Permalink to Alumna Spotlight:  Yvonne Lin">
          Alumna Spotlight:  Yvonne Lin
         </a>
        </h1>
       </header>
       <!-- .entry-header -->
       <p>
        Yvonne Lin (Class of 2013) graduated with a double major in Comparative Literature and French and a minor in Chinese. Since graduating, she has worked several jobs, including in client services at an investment firm in Washington and K-12 education in both the Bay Area and China.
        <a class="more-link" href="http://complit.berkeley.edu/featured/featured-alumna-yvonne-lin/#more-17931">
         » Read on »
        </a>
       </p>
      </article>
      <article class="group home-featured-item" id="post-17779">
       <figure class="home-featured-thumbnail">
        <a href="http://complit.berkeley.edu/featured/tim-hampton-on-the-humanities/" rel="bookmark" title="Permalink to Tim Hampton on the importance of an education in the Humanities">
         <img alt="" class="attachment-smportrait size-smportrait wp-post-image" height="154" sizes="(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px" src="http://complit.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/hampton.calday-768x789-150x154.jpg" srcset="http://complit.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/hampton.calday-768x789-150x154.jpg 150w, http://complit.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/hampton.calday-768x789-292x300.jpg 292w, http://complit.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/hampton.calday-768x789.jpg 768w, http://complit.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/hampton.calday-768x789-146x150.jpg 146w, http://complit.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/hampton.calday-768x789-100x103.jpg 100w" width="150">
