      <header class="home-bucket-item-header">
       <h1 class="home-bucket-item-title">
        <a href="http://complit.berkeley.edu/bob-alter-at-magnes-on-new-translation-of-hebrew-bible/" rel="bookmark" title="Permalink to Robert Alter at Magnes Center on his new translation of Hebrew Bible">
         Robert Alter at Magnes Center on his new translation of Hebrew Bible
        </a>
       </h1>
      </header>
      <!-- .entry-header -->
      <figure class="home-featured-thumbnail">
       <a href="http://complit.berkeley.edu/bob-alter-at-magnes-on-new-translation-of-hebrew-bible/" rel="bookmark" title="Permalink to Robert Alter at Magnes Center on his new translation of Hebrew Bible">
        <img alt="" class="attachment-news size-news wp-post-image" height="86" sizes="(max-width: 100px) 100vw, 100px" src="http://complit.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/alter_robert-100x86.jpg" srcset="http://complit.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/alter_robert-100x86.jpg 100w, http://complit.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/alter_robert-150x129.jpg 150w, http://complit.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/alter_robert-300x257.jpg 300w, http://complit.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/alter_robert.jpg 350w" width="100">
        </img>
       </a>
      </figure>
      <div dir="auto">
       Robert Alter, UC Berkeley Professor of Hebrew and Comparative Literature, chooses his words carefully—in conversation and in writing. Wednesday’s panel at the Magnes Center celebrated Alter’s latest feat—north of 3,500-pages and decades in the making—a decidedly literary translation of the Hebrew Bible into English.  Others in the panel were English Professor and poet Robert Hass, Professor of Near Eastern Studies and Hebrew scholar Ronald Hendel, and Professor of History and Religion Jonathan Sheehan.
      </div>
      <p>
       <a class="more-link" href="http://complit.berkeley.edu/bob-alter-at-magnes-on-new-translation-of-hebrew-bible/#more-18264">
        » Read on »
       </a>
      </p>
     </article>
