         Niklaus Largier presents at Sawyer Seminar on Religion
        </a>
       </h1>
      </header>
      <!-- .entry-header -->
      <figure class="home-featured-thumbnail">
       <a href="http://complit.berkeley.edu/niklaus-largier-presents-at-sawyer-seminar-on-religion/" rel="bookmark" title="Permalink to Niklaus Largier presents at Sawyer Seminar on Religion">
        <img alt="" class="attachment-news size-news wp-post-image" height="80" sizes="(max-width: 100px) 100vw, 100px" src="http://complit.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/largier.sawyer.religion-100x80.jpg" srcset="http://complit.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/largier.sawyer.religion-100x80.jpg 100w, http://complit.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/largier.sawyer.religion-150x120.jpg 150w, http://complit.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/largier.sawyer.religion-300x239.jpg 300w, http://complit.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/largier.sawyer.religion-768x612.jpg 768w, http://complit.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/largier.sawyer.religion-1024x817.jpg 1024w, http://complit.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/largier.sawyer.religion.jpg 1175w" width="100"/>
       </a>
      </figure>
      <p>
       Niklaus Largier—UC Berkeley Professor of German and Comparative Literature—joins forces with Professors Mayanthi Fernando and Michael Warner—of UC Santa Cruz and Yale, respectively—for one of a series of Sawyer Seminars orbiting “religious objects, rituals, and encounters.”
